<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="10Feb1927"><font color="red">10 February 1927</font> <i>BLHW</i> (to Harriet Weaver): Your second letter is worse than the first. Your accusation that I am wasting my talent is such a grave one that I should prefer to think out my doubtful and discouraged defence &hellip; Dunning &hellip; Roth has offered through a lawyer offering $1000 if I will admit that he offered this before publication. I am not replying. </div>
